d 'FCOINT': module to perform Fourier cointegration tests for time series with smooth structural breaks
d
d    fcoint implements four Fourier-based cointegration tests for
d time-series data. The tests use    low-frequency Fourier
d (trigonometric) components to approximate smooth structural
d breaks of    unknown form in the deterministic trend, without
d needing to estimate the number, timing, or form    of breaks.   
d This is important because conventional cointegration tests
d (Engle-Granger, Johansen, ADL) can	fail to detect
d cointegration when the equilibrium relationship has undergone
d smooth structural    shifts — such as gradual policy changes,
d evolving market structures, or slow institutional    reforms.   
d The key idea is that a Fourier expansion sin(2{c pi}kt/T) +
d cos(2{c pi}kt/T) can approximate    virtually any smooth
d deterministic function, including functions with multiple breaks
d and	 nonlinear shifts (Gallant, 1981). This avoids the pitfalls
d of dummy-variable approaches, which	 require pre-specifying
d break dates and forms. 
d
d KW: cointegration
d KW: Fourier
d KW: time series
d KW: structural breaks
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260307
d
d Author:   Merwan Roudane, NA
d Support: email  merwanroudane920@@gmail.com
d
